description:
&lt;p&gt;The Medical Microbiology Laboratory is UKAS accredited. We are also an approved HCPC training centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department performs 350,000 tests per year and is equipped with a Film Array, Virtuo blood culture system, Uri Mast, MicroScan, Maldi-tof, Ampliprep and Taqman, Viper XTR, BD Max,COVID-19 PCR, COVID-19 Antibody, (Bactalert TB) and Roche Cobas. Future planned developments include introduction Enteric PCR and Respiratory Multiplex PCR.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bedford and Luton &amp; Dunstable hospital sites are looking for people to help with the increased demand in Covid-19 testing. Can you help? These roles are for people who are looking for Pathology lab experience, have A-levels with some science background and want to help - HCPC Registration is not required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You need to be available for work 8am to 8pm so that we can extend the hours of the laboratory and increase the number of tests we can do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2 x 37.5 Full time (12 month fixed term contract) at Bedford Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2 x 37.5 Full time (12 month fixed term contract) at Luton and Dunstable Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Siobhan Holland - Laboratory Manager - siobhan.holland@bedfordhospital.nhs.uk or Anne George - Senior Biomedical Scientist - anne.goerge@ldh.nhs.uk  &lt;/p&gt;
